2
1 (3) A processing period is tolled from the date that a permit
2 applicant submits a petition under section 1315(1) until the date
3 that a decision of the director is made under section 1315(6). If a
4 permit applicant submits a petition under section 1315(1), the
5 department shall not approve or deny the application for the permit
6 under subsection (1) until after the director issues a decision
7 under section 1315(6).
8 (4) The approval or denial of department shall approve or deny
9 an application for a permit shall be in writing. and shall The
10 approval or denial must be based upon on evidence that would meet
11 the standards in section 75 of the administrative procedures act of
12 1969, 1969 PA 306, MCL 24.275, and the department shall cite to the
13 applicable statutory basis for the determination.
14 (5) Approval of an application for a permit may be granted
15 with conditions or modifications necessary to achieve compliance
16 with the part or parts of this act under which the permit is
17 issued.
18 (6) A denial of If an application for a permit is denied or,
19 for a permit under part 301 or 303, an approval the application for
20 the permit is approved with modification, of an application for a
21 permit shall the denial or approval with modification must
22 document, and any review upholding the denial or modification shall
23 must determine, to the extent practical, all of the following:
24 (a) That the decision is based on specifically cited
25 provisions of this act or rules promulgated under this act.
26 (b) That the decision is based upon on sufficient facts or
27 data , which that are recorded in the file.
28 (c) To the extent applicable, all both of the following:
29 (i) That the decision is the product of reliable scientific
RMH H06481'26 (H-1) n51d43

3
1 principles and methods.
2 (ii) That the decision has applied the principles and methods
3 reliably to the facts.
4 (d) In the case of denial of an application for a permit under
5 part 301 or 303, suggestions on changes to allow the permit to be
6 approved.
7 (7) Except for permits described in subsection (8), if the
8 department fails to satisfy the requirements of subsection (1) with
9 respect to an application for a permit, the department shall pay
10 the applicant an amount equal to 15% of the greater of the
11 following, as applicable:
12 (a) The total amount of the application fee for that permit.
13 (b) If an assessment or other fee is charged on an annual or
14 other periodic basis by the department to a person holding that
15 holds the permit for which the application was submitted, the total
16 amount of the first periodic charge of that assessment or other fee
17 for that permit.
18 (8) If the department fails to satisfy the requirements of
19 subsection (1) with respect to a permit required by section 11509,
20 11512, 30304, or 32603, the application shall be is considered to
21 be approved and the department shall be is considered to have made
22 any determination required for approval.
23 (9) The failure of the department to satisfy the requirements
24 of subsection (1) or the fact that the department is required to
25 make a payment under subsection (7) or is considered to have
26 approved a permit under subsection (8) shall must not be used by
27 the department as the basis for discriminating against the
28 applicant. If the department is required to make a payment under
29 subsection (7), the application shall must be processed in sequence
RMH H06481'26 (H-1) n51d43

4
1 with other applications for the same type of permit, based on the
2 date on which the processing period began, unless the director
3 determines on an application-by-application basis that the public
4 interest is best served by processing in a different order.
5 (10) If the department fails to satisfy the requirements of
6 subsection (1) with respect to 10% or more of the applications for
7 a particular type of permit received during a quarter of the state
8 fiscal year, the department shall immediately devote resources from
9 that program to eliminate any backlog and satisfy the requirements
10 of subsection (1) with respect to new applications for that type of
11 permit within the next fiscal quarter.
12 (11) If the department fails to satisfy the requirements of
13 subsection (1), the director shall notify the appropriations
14 committees of the senate and house of representatives of the
15 failure. The notification shall must be in writing and shall
16 include both of the following:
17 (a) An explanation of the reason for the failure.
18 (b) A statement of the amount the department was required to
19 pay the applicant under subsection (7) or a statement that the
20 department was required to consider the application to be approved
21 under subsection (8), as applicable.
22 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
23 unless all of the following bills of the 103rd Legislature are
24 enacted into law:
25 (a) House Bill No. 5937.
26 (b) House Bill No. 5938.
27 (c) House Bill No. 6038.
